<!DOCTYPE html>

<html>
	
	<head>
		<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.0.0/css/bootstrap.min.css" integrity="sha384-Gn5384xqQ1aoWXA+058RXPxPg6fy4IWvTNh0E263XmFcJlSAwiGgFAW/dAiS6JXm" 			 crossorigin="anonymous">
		<link rel="stylesheet" href="../stylesheets/main.css">
		
		<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
		<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
		<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Cairo:wght@300&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
	</head>
	
	
	
	<body class="show-body">
		
		
		
		<nav class="navbar navbar-expand-lg navbar-dark bg-dark homepage-navbar">
			<ul class="navbar-nav">
				<li class="nav-item">
					<a class="navbar-brand" href="/countries">Program</a>
				</li>
			</ul>
			
			<% if(!currentUser) { %>
				<ul class="navbar-nav ml-auto">
					<li class="nav-item ml-auto">
						<a class="nav-link" href="/login">Login</a>	
					</li>
				
					<li class="nav-item ml-auto">
						<a class="nav-link" href="register">Register</a>
					</li>
				</ul>
			<% } else { %>
			
				<ul class="navbar-nav ml-auto">
					<li class="nav-item homepage-screenNameli">
						Welcome, <em><%= currentUser.screenName %></em>
					</li>
					
					<li class="nav-item">
						<a class="nav-link" href="/logout">Logout</a>
					</li>
					
					<li class="nav-item">
						<a class="nav-link" href="/account">View Account</a>
					</li>
				</ul>
			
			<% } %>
		</nav>
		
		
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center show-name">
			<h1 class="show-h1">
				Estonia
			</h1>
		</div>
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center show-lesson">
			<h5 class="show-h5">
				Lesson 28
			</h5>
		</div>
			
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<img class="show-flag" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8f/Flag_of_Estonia.svg/255px-Flag_of_Estonia.svg.png">
		</div>
		
		<div class='d-flex justify-content-center show-firstquickfacth4'>
			<h4>Capital: Tallinn</h4>
		</div>
		
		<div class='d-flex justify-content-center show-quickfactsh4'>
			<h4>Population: 1.3 million</h4>
		</div>
		
		<div class='d-flex justify-content-center show-quickfactsh4'>
			<h4>Gross Domestic Product (GDP): 31.5 billion dollars</h4>
		</div>
		
		<div class='d-flex justify-content-center show-quickfactsh4'>
			<h4>Gross Domestic Product (GDP) Per Capita: 24,000 dollars</h4>
		</div>
		
		
		
		<hr class="show-hr1">	
		
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<figure>
				<img class="show-img1 show-map" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/f/fd/Estonia_in_Europe.svg">
				<span class="d-flex justify-content-center">
				</span>
			</figure>
		</div>
		
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				The Republic of Estonia is located on the east coast of the Baltic Sea, in northern Europe. Estonia was inhabited in the year 9000 BC by early settlers. Ancient Estonians were the last people in Europe to accept Christianity in the 13th century. Estonia has been ruled by Germans, Swedes, Danes and most recently the Russians (Soviet Union) for centuries, but the Estonians' growing nationalism eventually won over the Russian domination, and they established independence in 1991. Today, Estonia is a developed country with high income levels, universal healthcare, and free university education.


			</p>
		</div>
		
		

		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<figure>
				<img class="show-img1" src="https://www.worldtravelguide.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/shu-Estonia-Tallinn-Old-Town-and-seaport-harbour-312025430-1440x823.jpg">
				<span class="d-flex justify-content-center">
					<em><figcaption>Estonia gained independance following the collapse of the Soviet Union</figcaption></em>
				</span>
			</figure>
		</div>
		
		
		
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				The Estonian capital is Tallinn, and their currency is the Estonian Kroon (EEK).
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
	
	
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<figure>
				<img class="show-img1" src="https://www.state.gov/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Estonia-2109x1406.jpg">
				<span class="d-flex justify-content-center">
					<em><figcaption>Tallinn, Estonia</figcaption></em>
				</span>
			</figure>
		</div>
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<h3 class="show-factsh3">
				Two unique facts about Estonia
			</h3>
		</div>
			
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				Estonia’s largest water fall, Jågala Falls, freezes over completely during winter!
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<figure>
				<img class="show-img1" src="https://i.pinimg.com/originals/95/c2/ed/95c2ed45c9dbdd5098064271f83059a8.png">
				<span class="d-flex justify-content-center">
					<em><figcaption>Jågala Falls, Estonia, during winter</figcaption></em>
				</span>
			</figure>
		</div>
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				Estonia has one of the highest number of meteorite craters in the world. Scientists believe that one meteor impact event 7500 years ago was so large that it was equivalent to a nuclear bomb impact.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<figure>
				<img class="show-img1" src="https://cdn.britannica.com/52/114552-050-E08DC3FD/largest-Kaali-jarv-Craters.jpg">
				<span class="d-flex justify-content-center">
					<em><figcaption>Kaali Crater on Saaremaa, and island of Estonia</figcaption></em>
				</span>
			</figure>
		</div>
		
		
		
		
		
		<% if(currentUser && currentUser.lessonsComplete.length > 1){ %>
			<% currentUser.lessonsComplete.forEach(function(lesson){ %>
				<% if(lesson == "estonia"){ %>
					<% lessonComplete = true %>
					<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
						<a href="/countries" class="show-returnHomebtn btn btn-light">
							Return to Program	
						</a>
					</div>
				<% } %>
			<% }) %>
		
			<% if(lessonComplete != true) {%>
					<form action="/countries/estonia/account" method="POST">
						<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
							<button class="show-incompleteLessonbtn btn btn-success">
								Complete Lesson
							</button>
						</div>
					</form>
				<% } %>
		<% } %>
		
		
		
		<% if(!currentUser) { %>
			<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
				<a href="/countries" class="show-returnHomebtn btn btn-light">
					Return to Program	
				</a>
			</div>
		<% } %>
	
		
	
		
	</body>
	
	
</html>